		<h3>Pothgul Viharaya</h3>
		
		<img src="POTHGUL VIHARAYA.webp" align="left" width="17%" height="28%" alt="Pothgul Viharaya">
		<p><font size="4.5px">Just behind the temple of tooth. Nice buddhist temple in a small hill. You can see the surrounding of kandy. Little stupa is there. Edge of the temple you can see the cemetery of english peoples.The Kandy branch of the buddhist tv channel also located inside this temple. Big load buddha's stratue also can see.	</font></p><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
		<hr>
		<h3 align="right">Pillaiyar Kovil</h3>
		
		<img src="Pillaiyar Kovil.jpg" align="right" width="17%" height="28%" alt="Asgiriya Maha Viharaya">
		<p><font size="4.5px">This holy place was founded during the early times of British rule when the Bogambara Lake extended as far as the present spot marking the lake road as its boundary. The devotees had commenced building a shrine for Ganesh after finding a statue of the god in well there. According to tradition, the final day Perahara of the four Devales in Kandy starts from Pulleyar Kovil after the water-cutting ceremony.</font></p><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
		<hr>
		
		<h3 align="left">St. Paul's Church</h3>
		
		<img src="St.Paul's.jpg" align="left" width="17%" height="28%" alt="Asgiriya Maha Viharaya">
		<p><font size="4.5px">St. Paul's Church (Sinhala: ශාන්ත පාවුළු දේවස්ථානය) is an Anglican church in the historical district of Kandy, Sri Lanka on sacred grounds west of the Temple of the Tooth.</font></p><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
